You must be as busy as
Mr. Jang Se Joon nowadays. Madam.

135
00:27:42.789 --> 00:27:44.989
Thank you for
taking the time to come here.

136
00:27:44.989 --> 00:27:45.989
No. not at all.

137
00:27:45.989 --> 00:27:49.289
Aren't you tired of seeing her face
already? You see her every day!

138
00:27:51.579 --> 00:27:54.689
Let's hear what she has to say.

139
00:27:54.689 --> 00:27:58.379
We did some investigating to see who
people would prefer as their First Lady

140
00:27:58.379 --> 00:28:04.099
and you were the most popular pick among
people in their twenties to seventies!

141
00:28:04.099 --> 00:28:05.169
What?

142
00:28:05.169 --> 00:28:10.379
So you're the most popular pick among all
the other potential First Ladies!

143
00:28:10.379 --> 00:28:12.289
Congratulations!

144
00:28:12.289 --> 00:28:15.689
- Oh. really? I am?
- Yes!

145
00:28:37.379 --> 00:28:38.579
Oh. come now.

146
00:28:38.579 --> 00:28:43.289
Everyone is praising you. calling
you the perfect supportive wife.

147
00:28:43.289 --> 00:28:45.289
Oh. it's not like that at all!

148
00:28:45.289 --> 00:28:48.879
I just make sure that
he eats breakfast. is all.

149
00:28:49.409 --> 00:28:52.879
Wait. so you make
the assemblyman's breakfast yourself?

150
00:28:53.729 --> 00:28:57.989
It's a bit embarrassing. but
I think I enabled some of his bad habits.

151
00:28:57.989 --> 00:29:03.189
He's such a picky eater that he won't
eat unless I make food for him myself.

152
00:29:03.189 --> 00:29:07.879
Oh. I see! You're famous for
being a great cook. after all.

153
00:29:07.879 --> 00:29:10.989
Oh. stop it. People might
actually believe you!

154
00:29:11.989 --> 00:29:17.429
The guests who visit our home
just say that to be kind.

155
00:29:17.429 --> 00:29:21.939
Wait. you tend to and prepare
food for your guests yourself?

156
00:29:21.939 --> 00:29:26.189
Yes. It's to the point that
it's embarrassing. though.

157
00:29:27.229 --> 00:29:29.489
Wow. you really are amazing.

158
00:29:57.513 --> 00:30:09.513


159
00:30:10.489 --> 00:30:12.289
No more. okay?

160
00:30:12.289 --> 00:30:15.189
Look at you. being so naughty.

161
00:30:15.689 --> 00:30:19.079
- Fine.
- Eh?

162
00:30:19.869 --> 00:30:22.689
I'll be really naughty today.

163
00:30:26.879 --> 00:30:28.989
Oh. look at you.

164
00:30:30.189 --> 00:30:31.989
Oh?

165
00:30:35.989 --> 00:30:37.789
I'll scold you if you
keep acting like this!

166
00:31:09.289 --> 00:31:11.489
[SOCIAL WELFARE PROMO TEAM]

167
00:31:20.879 --> 00:31:23.079
Make sure you have the camera
and record it properly.

168
00:31:23.079 --> 00:31:24.289
Yes. sir.

169
00:31:46.879 --> 00:31:48.489
Close the curtains.

170
00:32:02.539 --> 00:32:03.989
Why. you little...

171
00:32:05.079 --> 00:32:06.489
How dare you...

172
00:32:06.489 --> 00:32:09.579
Sleep tight.
It'll all be over soon.

173
00:32:22.879 --> 00:32:26.379
- You're not allowed here.
- Yeah. whatever.

174
00:33:13.679 --> 00:33:15.379
Granny!

175
00:33:15.879 --> 00:33:17.579
Granny!

176
00:33:18.679 --> 00:33:20.579
Granny. behind you!

177
00:33:23.379 --> 00:33:25.179
No! No!

178
00:34:18.079 --> 00:34:19.479
Is anyone there?

179
00:34:22.579 --> 00:34:23.689
What the...

180
00:34:25.579 --> 00:34:29.079
Station One. here.
Answer me! Anybody?

181
00:34:35.079 --> 00:34:36.979
- Sir! There's...
- Yeah. I'm on my way now.

182
00:34:36.979 --> 00:34:39.579
- Keep things safe there until then.
- Yes. sir.

183
00:34:43.079 --> 00:34:44.079
Damn it!

184
00:34:48.379 --> 00:34:49.379
Damn it!

185
00:35:00.689 --> 00:35:02.789
Please. get me out! Quickly!

186
00:35:22.979 --> 00:35:25.979
Please. get me out!
Quickly! Quickly!

187
00:35:27.979 --> 00:35:29.379
Move away from the door!

188
00:36:26.379 --> 00:36:29.979
Granny! Granny! Granny!

189
00:36:30.479 --> 00:36:31.879
Granny!

190
00:38:06.579 --> 00:38:09.079
Hurry.
The cops are here.

191
00:38:22.789 --> 00:38:27.879
- Move out!
- Move out!

192
00:38:36.879 --> 00:38:39.979
Granny.
Granny!

193
00:38:42.879 --> 00:38:45.979
Granny! Are you all right?

194
00:38:45.979 --> 00:38:47.379
What about the assemblyman?
What about the assemblyman!

195
00:38:47.379 --> 00:38:49.289
Thankfully. the door to
his room didn't go down.

196
00:38:49.289 --> 00:38:50.689
Call 911.

197
00:38:50.689 --> 00:38:52.379
Call 911!

198
00:38:55.079 --> 00:38:58.189
Requesting an ambulance!

199
00:38:58.979 --> 00:39:02.079
Please unlock the door
to the assemblyman's room.

200
00:39:02.079 --> 00:39:03.879
It's unlocked!

201
00:39:07.789 --> 00:39:11.789
Um. while we're on the topic
of you being a supportive wife...

202
00:39:11.789 --> 00:39:15.579
Hasn't there been talk of
the assemblyman's success

203
00:39:15.579 --> 00:39:19.879
being almost entirely
due to his in-laws?

204
00:39:22.079 --> 00:39:23.879
His in-laws?

205
00:39:25.079 --> 00:39:28.879
Oh. did he have some other in-laws
besides my own parents?

206
00:39:29.979 --> 00:39:31.979
That's funny.

207
00:39:31.979 --> 00:39:35.979
But still. you're the eldest daughter
of the chairman of JB Group.

208
00:39:35.979 --> 00:39:41.689
And it's true that JB Group is the most
powerful conglomerate in our country.

209
00:39:46.289 --> 00:39:50.689
To tell you the truth.
I feel a bit bad for my husband

210
00:39:50.689 --> 00:39:52.879
for having met a woman like me.

211
00:39:52.879 --> 00:39:57.639
If he'd met another woman

212
00:39:57.639 --> 00:40:03.079
he would've been a great
son-in-law for another family.

213
00:40:03.079 --> 00:40:08.879
Oh... it seems that there were
some difficulties in the past.

214
00:40:09.379 --> 00:40:11.479
My late father...

215
00:40:13.579 --> 00:40:17.789
really didn't want a son-in-law
who was in politics.

216
00:40:17.789 --> 00:40:20.479
Wait. then. The reason why
Chairman Choi. your late father

217
00:40:20.479 --> 00:40:23.879
cut off ties with
you. his daughter

218
00:40:23.879 --> 00:40:25.979
was because of the assemblyman?

219
00:40:29.289 --> 00:40:32.979
I apologize. It seems that
I touched on a sensitive topic.

220
00:40:33.289 --> 00:40:35.379
No. it's fine.

221
00:40:38.379 --> 00:40:45.879
Men and women both need to be
loyal to the one they love. don't they?

222
00:40:45.879 --> 00:40:49.879
You really loved the assemblyman
quite a lot. didn't you?

223
00:40:49.879 --> 00:40:54.379
To the point that you gave up your right
as an heir to the company for him.

224
00:40:55.479 --> 00:40:56.479
Yes.

225
00:40:57.789 --> 00:41:00.689
And truthfully. I still...

226
00:41:02.439 --> 00:41:04.189
respect that man.

227
00:41:12.189 --> 00:41:13.879
They're coming out!

228
00:41:17.379 --> 00:41:22.379
- What's going on?
- How's the assemblyman?

229
00:41:22.379 --> 00:41:25.979
- Please. say something!
- What's the current situation?

230
00:41:36.479 --> 00:41:38.789
He works at an advertisement company?

231
00:41:38.789 --> 00:41:40.079
Yes. sir.

232
00:41:41.189 --> 00:41:43.979
And yet he broke that thick glass?

233
00:41:52.879 --> 00:41:58.789
Then do you not have any
JB Group shares anymore. Madam?

234
00:41:58.789 --> 00:42:03.479
I know that you had quite a bit that you
inherited. even before your marriage.

235
00:42:08.579 --> 00:42:14.159
Oh. you mean the shares
I had when I was single?

236
00:42:14.159 --> 00:42:16.079
I already donated those
a long time ago.

237
00:42:16.689 --> 00:42:20.079
Oh. are you talking about
the Pyeongchang Scholarship Foundation?

238
00:42:20.079 --> 00:42:21.579
Yes.

239
00:42:22.229 --> 00:42:23.979
However. I heard that
there's a special relationship

240
00:42:23.979 --> 00:42:28.079
between you and two
of the board directors.

241
00:42:28.079 --> 00:42:35.979
If that's true. don't you still possess
a lot of JB Group shares in reality?

242
00:42:44.189 --> 00:42:47.189
Mr. PD! They want us to cut
the feed for a second.

243
00:42:47.189 --> 00:42:50.789
Anchor Jo! We'll continue
this after some commercials.

244
00:42:52.789 --> 00:42:57.979
Well. then. I'll hear the response
to your question after the commercials.

245
00:42:57.979 --> 00:43:00.189
We'll continue after
the commercial break!

246
00:43:04.213 --> 00:43:16.213


247
00:43:17.379 --> 00:43:18.879
Ji Yeon.

248
00:43:19.689 --> 00:43:21.079
Yeah. Yoo Jin?

249
00:43:21.079 --> 00:43:25.579
I thought I told you that I didn't
want to talk about that.

250
00:43:26.379 --> 00:43:34.789
Yoo Jin. Wouldn't it be less painful
for me to do this than anyone else?

251
00:43:36.189 --> 00:43:37.979
That's true.

252
00:43:39.079 --> 00:43:41.579
It'll a sore spot for me regardless
of who questions me about it.

253
00:43:41.579 --> 00:43:43.479
Everyone has a weakness.

254
00:43:49.189 --> 00:43:54.289
Just like the matter
regarding your son.

255
00:43:55.189 --> 00:43:57.789
All right. the commercial break will
soon be over. We'll be shooting now!

256
00:43:57.789 --> 00:43:59.579
Please turn on your mics!

257
00:44:00.379 --> 00:44:03.789
All right.
Shall we get started?

258
00:44:06.189 --> 00:44:09.689
Sorry. Yoo Jin.
I overdid it.

259
00:44:10.189 --> 00:44:12.129
Yeah. Ji Yeon.

260
00:44:12.129 --> 00:44:14.789
Let's just follow the script.
All right. honey?

261
00:44:30.379 --> 00:44:34.579
I was so touched by
your interview today. Madam.

262
00:44:34.579 --> 00:44:37.379
Really? Thank you.
I was so nervous!

263
00:44:37.379 --> 00:44:42.479
No! You looked so natural
and so beautiful!

264
00:44:44.189 --> 00:44:45.789
Can you step out for a bit?

265
00:44:45.789 --> 00:44:48.379
- What?
- I'm fine. I'll take off my makeup.

266
00:44:48.379 --> 00:44:51.079
- Thank you.
- Yes. Madam.

267
00:44:51.079 --> 00:44:52.579
Oh. wait.

268
00:44:57.479 --> 00:44:59.379
Thank you so much for today.

269
00:44:59.379 --> 00:45:02.979
I baked these cookies.
I'm not sure if they're any good. though.

270
00:45:02.979 --> 00:45:04.979
Oh. I'm so touched. Madam!

271
00:45:04.979 --> 00:45:07.789
Can I take a photo of these?

272
00:45:07.789 --> 00:45:12.289
What? Oh. no!
Stop it.

273
00:45:20.579 --> 00:45:24.079
I won't eat these
and treasure them forever!

274
00:45:25.479 --> 00:45:27.189
Thank you.

275
00:45:41.689 --> 00:45:43.379
Again?

276
00:45:43.379 --> 00:45:44.689
Who was behind it this time?

277
00:45:44.689 --> 00:45:47.189
The investigation hasn't
been concluded yet. but...

278
00:45:48.209 --> 00:45:50.289
but I believe that Assemblyman Park's
people were probably behind it.

279
00:45:51.189 --> 00:45:53.189
No doubt about it.

280
00:46:06.289 --> 00:46:09.079
Cookies that Madam
baked for me herself!

281
00:46:09.079 --> 00:46:12.189
Behind them is the bag that
Madam has used for 20 years.

282
00:46:12.189 --> 00:46:15.479
I respect you and
love you. Madam! Heart. heart!

283
00:46:15.479 --> 00:46:16.979
Hey. what are you doing?

284
00:46:16.979 --> 00:46:18.789
Man. I respect her so much.

285
00:46:18.789 --> 00:46:21.189
Madam made these herself!

286
00:46:21.189 --> 00:46:22.689
Really?

287
00:46:22.689 --> 00:46:24.189
- Give me one!
- No!

288
00:46:24.189 --> 00:46:26.079
These are my new
family heirlooms!

289
00:46:26.079 --> 00:46:28.879
Geez. you're so stingy.
Let me see the photo. though.

290
00:46:28.879 --> 00:46:30.379
Wow!

291
00:46:42.189 --> 00:46:43.879
What shall we do. ma'am?

292
00:46:46.079 --> 00:46:49.439
Alter the scene of the crime

293
00:46:49.439 --> 00:46:52.189
so it seems like some unidentified
assailants attacked the office.

294
00:46:52.189 --> 00:46:54.189
Yes. ma'am.

295
00:46:55.079 --> 00:46:58.789
What... about that girl. then?

296
00:46:58.789 --> 00:47:01.789
Just leave her be for now.

297
00:47:02.579 --> 00:47:04.579
We'll definitely have
a use for her later.

298
00:47:04.579 --> 00:47:05.879
Yes. ma'am.

299
00:47:09.479 --> 00:47:11.289
That's fine for now.

300
00:47:22.189 --> 00:47:25.579
Looks like I'm getting
wrinkles in my old age.

301
00:47:27.289 --> 00:47:29.079
How old is she?

302
00:47:29.689 --> 00:47:31.079
Excuse me?

303
00:47:31.079 --> 00:47:34.139
That girl.

304
00:47:35.579 --> 00:47:39.479
She's in her late twenties.

305
00:47:41.579 --> 00:47:44.479
At least she's not a minor.

306
00:47:52.879 --> 00:47:54.559
It's me.

307
00:47:54.559 --> 00:47:58.189
Wait. so. am I eating breakfast
that you made starting tomorrow?

308
00:48:01.789 --> 00:48:04.379
Nice show you put on there.

309
00:48:05.289 --> 00:48:09.579
Yes. I trusted that
you'd take care of it.

310
00:48:10.149 --> 00:48:15.289
Also. about that
banner hanger...

311
00:48:15.289 --> 00:48:17.789
please take good care of
that for me.

312
00:48:19.189 --> 00:48:24.289
It seems like the rascal
got a good look at my face.

313
00:48:24.289 --> 00:48:27.979
The banner... hanger?

314
00:48:33.079 --> 00:48:34.529
Fine.

315
00:48:45.009 --> 00:48:46.879
President.

316
00:48:46.879 --> 00:48:48.319
Yes.

317
00:48:51.479 --> 00:48:53.579
Is there something that
you're hiding from me?

318
00:48:53.579 --> 00:48:56.789
What? Oh. Madam!
Of course not!

319
00:48:56.789 --> 00:48:57.979
How could I ever...

320
00:48:57.979 --> 00:49:00.979
I really shouldn't be like this

321
00:49:00.979 --> 00:49:03.079
but I'm starting to get
quite suspicious.

322
00:49:03.079 --> 00:49:05.379
Oh. Madam!
It's not like that at all!

323
00:49:05.379 --> 00:49:08.079
I just didn't want you to bother
you with unnecessary burdens

324
00:49:08.079 --> 00:49:09.379
so I was going to take
care of it myself. and then...

325
00:49:09.379 --> 00:49:12.189
Oh. yes. I apologize.
I'll remember that. ma'am.

326
00:49:12.189 --> 00:49:14.479
I'll be sure to take care of it
and report back to you.

327
00:49:14.479 --> 00:49:17.689
Yes. yes.
Please get some rest.

328
00:49:19.789 --> 00:49:23.289
Damn it. how did she
find out already?

329
00:49:23.789 --> 00:49:25.579
The men are on their way. right?

330
00:49:25.579 --> 00:49:28.189
Yes. They'll catch them soon.

331
00:49:29.069 --> 00:49:32.789
Why do I have to go to all this
trouble because of some banner hanger?

332
00:49:57.789 --> 00:50:00.289
- This is the only footage we got?
- Yes. sir.

333
00:50:02.189 --> 00:50:04.189
Wait. Rewind.

334
00:50:05.689 --> 00:50:06.789
Yeah. right there.

335
00:50:11.079 --> 00:50:12.789
No way.
Could it be?

336
00:50:27.813 --> 00:50:39.813


337
00:50:40.879 --> 00:50:43.189
Yes. Chief Jo.

338
00:50:43.189 --> 00:50:44.979
Please recall the men.

339
00:50:44.979 --> 00:50:45.979
Say what. now?

340
00:50:45.979 --> 00:50:48.589
If you don't. all those men
may die at his hands.

341
00:50:50.189 --> 00:50:52.289
What do you mean by that?

342
00:51:17.979 --> 00:51:19.589
Chief Jo!

343
00:51:19.589 --> 00:51:23.739
You sure have gotten funnier
nowadays. but that's really a hoot.

344
00:51:23.739 --> 00:51:26.319
- Our men are in danger!
- Wait. wait.

345
00:51:26.319 --> 00:51:27.879
So what you're telling
me. is that you. Colonel Jo...

346
00:51:27.879 --> 00:51:29.479
oh. I mean. Chief Jo.

347
00:51:29.479 --> 00:51:33.589
He's someone who you trained
while you were in the special forces?

348
00:51:33.589 --> 00:51:34.589
Yes.

349
00:51:55.089 --> 00:51:56.589
All right. then.

350
00:51:56.589 --> 00:52:02.589
I feel like you're trying to tell me that
he's the strongest agent you trained...

351
00:52:02.589 --> 00:52:05.189
- No. that's not it. sir!
- Chief Jo!

352
00:52:05.189 --> 00:52:08.189
I don't think you quite
get what I'm saying.

353
00:52:08.189 --> 00:52:14.479
I even sent my offensive team to catch
one measly banner-hanger.

354
00:52:14.479 --> 00:52:16.089
Do you get that?

355
00:52:16.089 --> 00:52:21.289
This is the offensive team of JSS.
the best security company in Korea!

356
00:52:22.289 --> 00:52:25.979
You'll soon come to realize
what I'm saying.

357
00:52:27.879 --> 00:52:29.589
Why. that little...

358
00:52:29.589 --> 00:52:32.289
That impudent bastard!

359
00:52:32.879 --> 00:52:34.189
Why. I never!

360
00:53:08.379 --> 00:53:09.789
Leave at once.

361
00:56:00.979 --> 00:56:03.979
Sir! Sir!

362
00:56:03.979 --> 00:56:05.479
Sir!

363
00:56:06.879 --> 00:56:07.879
Sir!

364
00:57:44.589 --> 00:57:47.089
Hey!
What happened?

365
00:57:51.979 --> 00:57:53.979
What happened. damn it?

366
00:58:00.689 --> 00:58:02.189
What a relief.

367
00:58:02.789 --> 00:58:04.089
Sir?

368
00:58:04.189 --> 00:58:06.849
What do you mean
you're relieved. Chief?

369
00:58:06.849 --> 00:58:08.089
Nobody's dead.

370
00:58:25.189 --> 00:58:27.479
Why are you here
in the living room?

371
00:58:28.589 --> 00:58:32.789
It seems that I'll be sleeping late today
since there are matters to attend to.

372
00:58:33.689 --> 00:58:38.979
Why? Is there someone else causing
trouble around here besides me?

373
00:58:53.979 --> 00:58:56.289
Your daughter. Assemblyman.

374
00:59:14.589 --> 00:59:16.289
What about Anna?

375
00:59:18.589 --> 00:59:20.979
She ran away again.

376
00:59:22.589 --> 00:59:25.089
She should have
matured a bit by now.

377
00:59:25.089 --> 00:59:26.689
But it seems not.

378
00:59:38.479 --> 00:59:40.979
Maybe it's because the apple
doesn't fall far from the tree?

379
00:59:53.879 --> 00:59:55.979
If something bad
happens to that child...

380
00:59:59.379 --> 01:00:03.189
our contract is null and void.
You know that. right?

381
01:02:09.979 --> 01:02:11.289
What's going on?

382
01:02:12.589 --> 01:02:14.479
What's with that woman?

383
01:02:48.589 --> 01:02:49.979
[SLEEPING PILLS]

384
01:02:57.089 --> 01:03:02.189
No. No way.

385
01:03:18.689 --> 01:03:21.689
Subtitles by DramaFever

386
01:03:31.369 --> 01:03:33.879
So what you're saying is
you lost that banner hanger.

387
01:03:33.879 --> 01:03:37.479
He's not someone that can
be caught by JSS.

388
01:03:37.479 --> 01:03:38.479
Who sent you?

389
01:03:38.479 --> 01:03:41.789
If I come to see you
for a second time. you'll die.

390
01:03:41.789 --> 01:03:43.479
You were in the wrong
place at the wrong time

391
01:03:43.479 --> 01:03:45.089
and saw something
you shouldn't have.

392
01:03:45.089 --> 01:03:46.979
I'm sorry.

393
01:03:46.979 --> 01:03:49.479
You're pretty. just like your mother.

394
01:03:49.479 --> 01:03:54.119
I remember everything.
Mom didn't commit suicide.

395
01:03:54.119 --> 01:03:59.289
She's the reason why I've been forced
to obey Choi Yoo Jin's every whim.
